#. §22: `z`
#. §23: `g`
#. §24: `g * z * g⁻¹ = z`
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L07_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing **The Center**!\n"
"\n"
"You proved that a group is abelian if and only if its center is the\n"
"whole group:\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"Both directions used the same two tools — §1 and\n"
"§2 — in opposite order:\n"
"- **Forward**: §3 extracts universal membership from the\n"
"  hypothesis, then §4 reduces commutativity\n"
"  to center membership.\n"
"- **Backward**: §5 reduces the goal to universal membership,\n"
"  then §6 reduces each membership to commutativity.\n"
"\n"
"The center Z(G) measures the distance from abelianness:\n"
"- §7 means fully commutative\n"
"- §8 means only §9 commutes with everything (\"centerless\")\n"
"- In between, §10 captures the abelian core\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"Z(G) = G iff ∀ x, y: xy = yx. Forward: if Z(G) = G,\n"
"every y ∈ Z(G), so xy = yx. Backward: if xy = yx for all x, y,\n"
"then every z commutes with all g, so z ∈ Z(G).\"*\n"
"\n"
"Your new tools from this world:\n"
"\n"
"| Item | Type | Purpose |\n"
"|------|------|---------|\n"
"| §11 | Definition | The center (elements commuting with everything) |\n"
"| §12 | Theorem | §13 |\n"
"| §14 | Theorem | §15 |\n"
"\n"
"Notice the asymmetry: Level 5 used §16, so §17\n"
"was an axiom. Here both directions used only §18 — you\n"
"extracted commutativity from the hypothesis instead. A §19\n"
"is exactly a §20 where §21 holds by\n"
"definition. What you proved is: the center characterizes exactly\n"
"when this extra axiom holds.\n"
"\n"
"The center will appear again: it is always a **normal** subgroup\n"
"(the proof is immediate — if §22 commutes with §23, then\n"
"§24), and the center of a **p-group** is always\n"
"non-trivial (a key step in classifying finite groups)."
msgstr ""

