#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L01_MulComm
msgid "You've met §0, the defining property of a commutative group.\n"
"\n"
"Notice the type signature: we wrote §1 instead of\n"
"§2. This tells Lean that §3 is commutative, which makes\n"
"§4 available. If you tried to use §5 with only\n"
"§6, Lean would refuse — it doesn't know the group is\n"
"commutative.\n"
"\n"
"Remember the shoes-and-socks lemma from Group Basics:\n"
"§7, where the order *reversed*. With\n"
"§8, you could rearrange that back to §9 — no\n"
"reversal needed. That's the connection the earlier world promised.\n"
"\n"
"In a §10, you can freely rearrange the order of factors.\n"
"But *which* factors you swap matters when there are more than two.\n"
"In the next level, you'll learn to direct §11 at specific\n"
"pairs."
msgstr ""

