#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L09_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing **Cyclic Groups**!\n"
"\n"
"You proved the cornerstone result: **a group of prime order is\n"
"cyclic**. Any non-identity element generates the entire group.\n"
"\n"
"The proof is the **dichotomy-plus-contradiction** pattern applied\n"
"to §0:\n"
"1. In a prime-order group, every subgroup is §1 or §2\n"
"   (Lagrange + primality)\n"
"2. §3 is a subgroup, so §4\n"
"3. If §5, then §6 (by §7) —\n"
"   contradiction with §8\n"
"4. So §9 — §10 generates §11\n"
"5. Therefore §12 is cyclic\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"Let §13 be prime, and let §14 with §15.\n"
"The subgroup §16 generated by §17 has order dividing §18, so its\n"
"order is §19 or §20. Since §21, the order is not §22, so it\n"
"must be §23. Therefore §24 and §25 is cyclic.\"*\n"
"\n"
"**Caution**: the converse is false. Not every cyclic group has prime\n"
"order — §26 is cyclic with infinite order, and §27 is cyclic\n"
"with non-prime order. Prime order *implies* cyclic, but cyclic does\n"
"not imply prime order.\n"
"\n"
"Your new tools from this world:\n"
"\n"
"| Item | Type | Purpose |\n"
"|------|------|---------|\n"
"| §28, §29, §30 | Theorem | Integer power identities |\n"
"| §31 | Definition | Subgroup generated by §32 |\n"
"| §33 | Theorem | §34 |\n"
"| §35 | Theorem | §36 |\n"
"| §37 | Definition | Order of an element |\n"
"| §38 | Theorem | §39 |\n"
"| §40 | Definition | §41 is cyclic |\n"
"| §42 | Theorem | §43 |\n"
"| §44 | Theorem | Prime order ⇒ subgroups are ⊥ or ⊤ |\n"
"| §45 | Tactic | Close decidable goals |\n"
"| §46 | Tactic | Reduce any goal to §47 |\n"
"\n"
"The result you proved — groups of prime order are cyclic — will\n"
"reappear in the **Lagrange** world, where you'll prove that\n"
"prime-order groups have no nontrivial proper subgroups. It also\n"
"drives the classification of small groups via **Sylow theory**."
msgstr ""

