#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L02_ZpowersMem
msgid "Given an element §0 of a group §1, the set of all integer powers\n"
"of §2 forms a subgroup. This subgroup is called §3:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"It is the smallest subgroup containing §5 — the subgroup *generated*\n"
"by §6.\n"
"\n"
"The key membership lemma is §7:\n"
"\n"
"§8\n"
"\n"
"To show §9, rewrite with §10 and then\n"
"provide the integer exponent that works.\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: The §11 in this world is integer power (§12), not the\n"
"natural-number §13 from CommGroupIntro. They look identical but are\n"
"different operations internally. In particular, §14 does **not**\n"
"apply to §15 — you need §16 instead. If you see\n"
"a confusing \"did not find occurrence\" error after §17,\n"
"that's why. Always use the §18 lemmas for integer exponents.\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §19 is in §20 by finding the right exponent."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `a : G`
#. §1: `a⁻¹`
#. §2: `⁻¹`
#. §3: `\\inv`
#. §4: `\\-1`
#. §5: `mul_inv_cancel`
#. §6: `a * a⁻¹ = 1`
#. §7: `a * a⁻¹ * b = b`
#. §8: `(a * a⁻¹) * b = b`
#. §9: `a * a⁻¹`
#. §10: `mul_inv_cancel`
#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial.L03_RightInverse
msgid "Every element in a group has an **inverse**. If §0, then §1 is its\n"
"inverse. The superscript §2 is typed as §3 or §4 in Lean.\n"
"\n"
"The theorem §5 says that §6 — multiplying an\n"
"element by its inverse on the right gives the identity.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, the goal is §7. Remember that multiplication\n"
"is **left-associated**: this means §8. So §9\n"
"appears as a sub-expression on the left, and §10 applies to it."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `a`
#. §1: `f`
#. §2: `b * a * b⁻¹`
#. §3: `f(a) = 1`
#. §4: `f(b * a * b⁻¹) = f(b) · f(a) · f(b)⁻¹ = f(b) · 1 · f(b)⁻¹ = 1`
#. §5: `b * a * b⁻¹ ∈ ker(f)`
#. §6: `mem_ker`
#. §7: `f`
#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L03_KernelConjugation
msgid "If §0 is in the kernel of §1, what about §2?\n"
"\n"
"Since §3:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"So §5 too. The kernel \"absorbs\" conjugation.\n"
"\n"
"The proof combines kernel reasoning (unfold §6) with the\n"
"hom-property move (push §7 through the expression)."
