#. §0: `simp`
#. §1: `«{h}»`
#. §2: `simp [«{h}»]`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L02_DirectedSimp
msgid "Bare §0 won't work here — it doesn't know about §1.\n"
"Try §2 to include the hypothesis."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `⊤`
#. §1: `apply Subgroup.mk_carrier`
#. §2: `intro`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L10_WholeGroupSubgroup
msgid "The whole group is a subgroup of itself — the largest possible\n"
"subgroup. In Lean, this is called §0 (\"top\").\n"
"\n"
"The math was trivial here, but the pattern was the same:\n"
"\n"
"1. §1 — creates three obligations\n"
"2. For each obligation: §2 the hypotheses, then prove the claim.\n"
"\n"
"You've now built two subgroups: the trivial subgroup (the smallest)\n"
"and the whole group (the largest). In the boss, you'll build one\n"
"where the closure proofs require real algebra: the centralizer."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `(a * b) * (a * b) = a * a * (b * b)`
#. §1: `intro a b`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L07_BuildAHom
msgid "Now prove that squaring preserves multiplication:\n"
"§0.\n"
"\n"
"First, §1 to name the elements."
