#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L03_PowerNotation
msgid "§0 does it in two\n"
"steps. Or expand fully: §1."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `intro x y`
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L07_Boss
msgid "Now §0 to introduce the elements."
msgstr ""

#. §0: ```
#. a = b
#.   ← a * b⁻¹ = 1          (mul_inv_eq_one)
#.   ← a * b⁻¹ ∈ ⊥          (mem_bot)
#.   ← a * b⁻¹ ∈ ker(f)     (ker = ⊥)
#.   ← f(a * b⁻¹) = 1       (mem_ker)
#.   ← f(a) · f(b)⁻¹ = 1    (map_mul, map_inv)
#.   ← f(b) · f(b)⁻¹ = 1    (hab)
#.   ✓                        (mul_inv_cancel)
#. ```
#. §1: `f(a) = f(b)`
#. §2: `f(ab⁻¹) = f(a)f(b)⁻¹ = 1`
#. §3: `ab⁻¹ ∈ ker(f) = {1}`
#. §4: `ab⁻¹ = 1`
#. §5: `a = b`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L07_TrivialKernelEquals
msgid "That was the longest rewrite chain so far. Here's the full picture:\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"This is the **forward direction** of the boss theorem:\n"
"*trivial kernel → injective*.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"Since §1, we have\n"
"§2, so §3,\n"
"hence §4, so §5.\"*"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L01_SubgroupMembership
msgid "What Is a Subgroup?"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `inv_eq_of_mul_eq_one_right`
#. §1: `a⁻¹ = b⁻¹`
#. §2: `a * b⁻¹ = 1`
#. §3: `inv_inj`
#. §4: `inv_inj`
#. §5: `a⁻¹ = b⁻¹ → a = b`
#. §6: `inv_inv`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasicsPset.L06_MulInvEqOneImpliesEq
msgid "Two tools, two steps: §0 deduces\n"
"§1 from §2, and §3 strips the inverses.\n"
"\n"
"This is your first use of §4 — the fact that inversion is\n"
"injective (§5). It follows immediately from\n"
"§6: apply inversion to both sides and the double inverses\n"
"cancel. Keep it in mind for future problems involving inverse\n"
"equalities."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `a ∈ H ∧ a ∈ K`
#. §1: `exact ⟨hH, hK⟩`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L06_AngleBrackets
msgid "Now the goal is §0. Build the conjunction\n"
"with §1."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L02_RangeMulMem
msgid "Range Closed Under Multiplication"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `1 ∈ f.ker`
#. §1: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_ker]`
#. §2: `f 1 = 1`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L01_KernelDef
msgid "The goal is §0. Use §1 to\n"
"unfold this to §2."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `∀ (a : G), a ∈ H → a⁻¹ ∈ H`
#. §1: `∀`
#. §2: `→`
#. §3: `intro a ha`
#. §4: `a : G`
#. §5: `ha : a ∈ H`
#. §6: `a⁻¹ ∈ H`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L06_IntroTactic
msgid "The goal is §0. This has a\n"
"universal quantifier (§1) and an implication (§2).\n"
"\n"
"Use §3 to introduce both at once. This gives you\n"
"§4 and §5, and the goal becomes §6."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `MonoidHom.mem_ker`
#. §1: `f : G →* H`
#. §2: `x ∈ f.ker ↔ f x = 1`
#. §3: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_ker]`
#. §4: `f x = 1`
#. §5: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_ker] at h`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L01_KernelDef
msgid "§0 says: for a group homomorphism §1,\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"Use §3 to unfold kernel membership into\n"
"the equation §4, or use it at a hypothesis with\n"
"§5."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `G`
#. §1: `H`
#. §2: `f : G →* H`
#. §3: `f (a * b) = f a * f b`
#. §4: `a, b : G`
#. §5: `→*`
#. §6: `→`
#. §7: `MonoidHom`
#. §8: `MulOneClass`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L03_WhatIsAHom
msgid "A group homomorphism from §0 to §1. A function §2\n"
"satisfying §3 for all §4.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, the notation is §5 (not §6). The type name is §7\n"
"because the definition works for any §8, but it applies to\n"
"groups."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `apply MonoidHom.mk_fun (fun g => g * g)`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L07_BuildAHom
msgid "Use §0 to provide the\n"
"squaring function and set up the multiplication-preserving obligation."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `f(a) · f(b) = f(c)`
#. §1: `a · b · c⁻¹ ∈ ker(f)`
#. §2: `f`
#. §3: `f(x) = f(y)`
#. §4: `x · y⁻¹ ∈ ker(f)`
#. §5: `f(a) = f(b)`
#. §6: `f(ab⁻¹) = 1`
#. §7: `f(a) · f(b) = f(c)`
#. §8: `a · b · c⁻¹ ∈ ker(f)`
#. §9: `f`
#. §10: `f(abc⁻¹) = f(a)f(b)f(c)⁻¹ = f(c)f(c)⁻¹ = 1`
#. §11: `abc⁻¹ ∈ ker(f)`
#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L04_EquationToKernel
msgid "Given any equation §0 in the target, you\n"
"proved §1.\n"
"\n"
"This is the kernel's role as a measuring device: it captures the\n"
"\"difference\" between elements that §2 sends to the same place.\n"
"More precisely, §3 if and only if §4.\n"
"\n"
"The proof pattern is the reverse of the Homomorphisms boss:\n"
"there you started with §5 and derived §6;\n"
"here you started with §7 and derived\n"
"§8.\n"
"\n"
"This is the **kernel calculation**: unfold membership, push §9\n"
"through, substitute the kernel equation, cancel. You've now used\n"
"this pattern in three levels — recognizing it as a single move\n"
"will serve you well later, especially when proving kernels are\n"
"normal subgroups.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *§10,\n"
"so §11.*"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L01_DeriveLeftInverse
msgid "Deriving Left Inverse"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `zpow_zero`
#. §1: `a ^ (0 : ℤ) = 1`
#. §2: `zpow_one`
#. §3: `a ^ (1 : ℤ) = a`
#. §4: `zpow_neg`
#. §5: `a ^ (-n) = (a ^ n)⁻¹`
#. §6: `a ^ (-1 : ℤ)`
#. §7: `a⁻¹`
#. §8: `a ^ (-n : ℤ)`
#. §9: `(a ^ n)⁻¹`
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L01_ZpowBasics
msgid "Integer powers generalize natural-number powers by allowing negative\n"
"exponents. The three key identities are:\n"
"\n"
"- §0: §1\n"
"- §2: §3\n"
"- §4: §5\n"
"\n"
"In notation: §6 is just another way of writing §7,\n"
"and §8 is §9.\n"
"\n"
"Next: you'll see how integer powers give rise to the subgroup\n"
"*generated* by a single element."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `≤`
#. §1: `intro x hx`
#. §2: `hle`
#. §3: `H`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L02_InfPreservesLE
msgid "Unfold §0 with §1, unpack the intersection,\n"
"apply §2 to the §3-component, and rebuild."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `y₁ = f(x₁)`
#. §1: `y₂ = f(x₂)`
#. §2: `y₁ * y₂ = f(x₁) * f(x₂) = f(x₁ * x₂)`
#. §3: `x₁ * x₂`
#. §4: `y₁ * y₂`
#. §5: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_range] at h₁ h₂`
#. §6: `obtain ⟨x₁, hx₁⟩ := h₁`
#. §7: `obtain ⟨x₂, hx₂⟩ := h₂`
#. §8: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_range]`
#. §9: `use x₁ * x₂`
#. §10: `rw [map_mul, hx₁, hx₂]`
#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L02_RangeMulMem
msgid "In Kernel and Image you showed the range is closed under inverses.\n"
"Now show it's closed under multiplication.\n"
"\n"
"If §0 and §1, then §2.\n"
"So §3 is a witness for §4.\n"
"\n"
"The pattern:\n"
"1. Unfold both range hypotheses with §5\n"
"2. Extract witnesses: §6 and §7\n"
"3. Unfold the goal: §8\n"
"4. Provide the combined witness: §9\n"
"5. Verify: §10"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `inv_mul_cancel_left`
#. §1: `mul_one`
#. §2: `mul_inv_cancel`
#. §3: `mul_inv_cancel_right : (a * b) * b⁻¹ = a`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L06_RightCancel
msgid "Right cancellation mirrors left cancellation. Notice the asymmetry:\n"
"left cancellation used a single lemma (§0), but\n"
"right cancellation required a three-step chain each time. This traces\n"
"back to the axioms — §1 and §2 are right-sided,\n"
"so once we derived their left-sided counterparts (L01–L02), *left*\n"
"cancellation became easy to package. You could build\n"
"§3 to restore symmetry —\n"
"a natural exercise for a problem set.\n"
"\n"
"Both cancellation laws are now in your toolkit."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `rw [pow_zero, pow_zero, pow_zero, one_mul]`
#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L06_Boss
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L08_CentralizerMulMem
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L11_Boss
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L08_ObtainPractice
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L10_InfComm
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L10_InfComm
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L11_Boss
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L11_Boss
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L02_InfPreservesLE
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L03_LETransitive
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L04_BotInfEqBot
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L05_InverseCarrier
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L05_InverseCarrier
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L06_LEAntisymm
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L06_LEAntisymm
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L07_Boss
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L07_Boss
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L07_Boss
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L02_CenterOne
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L05_CenterEqTop
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L06_TopMeansAbelian
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L07_Boss
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L07_Boss
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L02_ZpowersMem
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L06_IsCyclic
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L07_PrimeDichotomy
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L08_ZpowersTopOfPrime
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L09_Boss
#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L07_Boss
msgid "§0"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `ext`
#. §1: `ext x`
#. §2: `H = K`
#. §3: `x ∈ H ↔ x ∈ K`
#. §4: `ext x`
#. §5: `↔`
#. §6: `refine ⟨?_, ?_⟩`
#. §7: `intro`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L09_ExtTactic
msgid "The §0 tactic proves two structures are equal by showing they\n"
"agree on all components.\n"
"\n"
"For subgroups, §1 reduces §2 to §3.\n"
"\n"
"This is the **extensionality principle**: subgroups with the same\n"
"elements are equal.\n"
"\n"
"After §4, split the §5 with §6, then prove\n"
"each direction with §7 and membership reasoning."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `b⁻¹`
#. §1: `mul_assoc`
#. §2: `mul_inv_cancel`
#. §3: `mul_one`
#. §4: `calc`
#. §5: ```
#. calc a = (a * b) * b⁻¹ := by rw [mul_assoc, mul_inv_cancel, mul_one]
#. _ = ...
#. ```
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L06_RightCancel
msgid "Same idea as left cancellation, but multiply by §0 on the\n"
"right. Each \" peel-off \" step chains three rewrites: §1 to\n"
"re-bracket, §2 to cancel the pair, and §3 to\n"
"clean up.\n"
"\n"
"Start a §4 block:\n"
"§5"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `a * (b * (b⁻¹ * c)) = a * c`
#. §1: `b * (b⁻¹ * c)`
#. §2: `(b * b⁻¹) * c`
#. §3: `rw [← mul_assoc]`
#. §4: `rw [← mul_assoc b b⁻¹ c]`
#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial.L07_TargetedRewriting
msgid "Now the goal should be §0.\n"
"You need to re-bracket §1 into §2.\n"
"\n"
"Since there are nested products, plain §3 might\n"
"target the wrong triple. Use explicit arguments:\n"
"§4."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `H ≤ ⊤`
#. §1: `⊤`
#. §2: `⊥ ≤ H`
#. §3: `⊥ ≤ H`
#. §4: `∀ x, x ∈ ⊥ → x ∈ H`
#. §5: `x ∈ ⊥`
#. §6: `x = 1`
#. §7: `Subgroup.mem_bot`
#. §8: `1 ∈ H`
#. §9: `one_mem H`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L04_BotLE
msgid "You've shown §0 — every subgroup sits below §1. Now prove\n"
"the other half: §2 — the trivial subgroup sits below everything.\n"
"\n"
"The proof unfolds §3 to §4. Given\n"
"§5, you know §6 (by §7). Once you\n"
"rewrite with this, the goal becomes §8, which is §9."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L08_ObtainPractice
msgid "Intersection Closure"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `MonoidHom`
#. §1: `G →* H`
#. §2: `→*`
#. §3: `→`
#. §4: `MonoidHom`
#. §5: `map_mul`
#. §6: `map_mul f a b : f (a * b) = f a * f b`
#. §7: `f : G →* H`
#. §8: `map_mul f a b`
#. §9: `f`
#. §10: `f (a * b) = f a * f b`
#. §11: `map_mul`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L03_WhatIsAHom
msgid "A **group homomorphism** is a function between groups that preserves\n"
"multiplication. In Lean 4 + Mathlib, group homomorphisms use the type\n"
"§0 with notation §1.\n"
"\n"
"⚠️ The notation is §2 (with a star), not §3 (plain function arrow).\n"
"The name §4 is used because the definition works for monoids\n"
"too — but it applies equally to groups.\n"
"\n"
"The defining property is §5:\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"Given §7, the lemma §8 tells you that §9\n"
"distributes over multiplication.\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §10 using §11."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `mul_left_cancel`
#. §1: `mul_right_cancel`
#. §2: `1`
#. §3: `a * e = a`
#. §4: `e * a = a`
#. §5: `a`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasicsPset.L03_RightMulImpliesOne
msgid "Left version used §0; right version used\n"
"§1. Together, these say that §2 is the *only* element\n"
"that leaves other elements unchanged under multiplication — in other\n"
"words, the identity element is characterized by the property §3\n"
"(or §4) for any §5.\n"
"\n"
"Whenever you see a common factor on one side, cancellation is the\n"
"right move."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `⊥`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L02_MemBot
msgid "The Trivial Subgroup §0"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `exact e`
#. §1: `e`
#. §2: `a * 1 = a`
#. §3: `mul_one a : a * 1 = a`
#. §4: `exact mul_one a`
#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial.L01_RightIdentity
msgid "§0 closes the goal if §1 has exactly the right type.\n"
"\n"
"For example, if the goal is §2 and §3,\n"
"then §4 closes the goal."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `mul_left_cancel`
#. §1: `a * b = a * c`
#. §2: `b = c`
#. §3: `exact mul_left_cancel h`
#. §4: `h : a * b = a * c`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L05_LeftCancel
msgid "§0 says that if §1, then §2.\n"
"\n"
"This is the **left cancellation law**: you can cancel a common left\n"
"factor in a group.\n"
"\n"
"To use it: §3 where §4."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `x ∈ H`
#. §1: `x⁻¹ ∈ H`
#. §2: `inv_mem`
#. §3: `inv_mem : x ∈ H → x⁻¹ ∈ H`
#. §4: `a⁻¹ ∈ H`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L03_InvMem
msgid "The third closure property: if §0, then §1.\n"
"\n"
"The theorem §2 captures this:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §4."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `G`
#. §1: `center G = {z : G | ∀ g : G, g * z = z * g}`
#. §2: `Subgroup.center G`
#. §3: `Subgroup.mem_center_iff`
#. §4: `z ∈ Subgroup.center G ↔ ∀ g, g * z = z * g`
#. §5: `rw [Subgroup.mem_center_iff]`
#. §6: `z`
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L01_CenterMem
msgid "The **center** of a group §0 is the subgroup of all elements that\n"
"commute with every other element:\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, this is §2. The key lemma for working with\n"
"the center is §3:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"This converts between the abstract \"membership in center\" and the\n"
"concrete \"commutes with everything\" condition. Almost every proof\n"
"about the center starts with §5.\n"
"\n"
"Given an element §6 that commutes with everything, show it's in the\n"
"center."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `apply Subgroup.mk_carrier`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L07_BuildingTrivial
msgid "Use §0 to set up the three closure\n"
"obligations."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `← mul_assoc`
#. §1: `a⁻¹ * a`
#. §2: `inv_mul_cancel`
#. §3: `one_mul`
#. §4: `calc`
#. §5: `calc a⁻¹ * (a * b)`
#. §6: `_ = ...`
#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial.L06_CalcBlocks
msgid "This is the same re-bracket / cancel / clean up pattern from\n"
"Level 5, but the parentheses need to move **leftward**.\n"
"\n"
"Plan your three steps:\n"
"1. Re-bracket leftward using §0\n"
"2. Cancel §1 using §2\n"
"3. Clean up with §3\n"
"\n"
"Write this as a §4 block. Start with §5 and\n"
"then write each §6 step."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L03_PowerNotation
msgid "Powers"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `⊤`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L03_LETop
msgid "Everything Is in §0"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L10_InfComm
msgid "Intersection Is Commutative"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `x⁻¹ * x`
#. §1: `x`
#. §2: `a`
#. §3: `x * a`
#. §4: `← hx`
#. §5: `x * a`
#. §6: `a * x`
#. §7: `x`
#. §8: `x⁻¹`
#. §9: `x * x⁻¹`
#. §10: `mul_inv_cancel`
#. §11: `a * 1`
#. §12: `a`
#. §13: `mul_one`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L09_CentralizerInvMem
msgid "**Step-by-step plan**: After prepending §0\n"
"on the left, re-associate so that §1 is adjacent to §2, giving\n"
"§3. Then use §4 to replace §5 with §6. Now\n"
"re-associate so §7 is adjacent to §8, and cancel §9\n"
"using §10. Finally simplify §11 to §12 with\n"
"§13."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `«{a}» * 1 = 1 * «{a}»`
#. §1: `mul_one`
#. §2: `one_mul`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L05_ShowTactic
msgid "Now the goal is §0. Use §1 and §2."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `True`
#. §1: `intro x y _ _`
#. §2: `trivial`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L10_WholeGroupSubgroup
msgid "**mul_mem**: If two elements satisfy §0, their product\n"
"does too.\n"
"\n"
"§1 to introduce and discard the trivial hypotheses,\n"
"then §2."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.GroupBasicsPset.L06_MulInvEqOneImpliesEq
msgid "Cancelling via Inverses"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `b * b⁻¹`
#. §1: `mul_inv_cancel`
#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial.L08_Boss
msgid "Cancel §0 with §1."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `x⁻¹ ∈ H`
#. §1: `(x⁻¹)⁻¹ ∈ H`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupPset.L05_InverseCarrier
msgid "**inv_mem**: You have §0 and need §1.\n"
"Which membership lemma gives this directly?"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `simp`
#. §1: `@[simp]`
#. §2: `simp`
#. §3: `simp [h1, h2]`
#. §4: `h1`
#. §5: `h2`
#. §6: `simp`
#. §7: `simp`
#. §8: `simp`
#. §9: `simp [specific_lemma]`
#. §10: `rw`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L01_SimpTactic
msgid "The §0 tactic simplifies the goal by repeatedly applying lemmas\n"
"tagged with §1.\n"
"\n"
"**Basic usage**: §2 tries all known simp lemmas automatically.\n"
"\n"
"**Directed usage**: §3 adds §4 and §5 to the lemma set.\n"
"Use this when bare §6 doesn't close the goal, or when you want to\n"
"include hypotheses from the context.\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: §7 is powerful but can be opaque. If §8 doesn't work,\n"
"try §9 or fall back to manual §10 steps."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Subgroup.mem_top`
#. §1: `⊤`
#. §2: `Subgroup.mem_top (x : G) : x ∈ (⊤ : Subgroup G)`
#. §3: `mem_bot`
#. §4: `↔`
#. §5: `exact Subgroup.mem_top x`
#. §6: `x ∈ ⊤`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L03_LETop
msgid "§0 says that every element belongs to the\n"
"whole group §1:\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"Unlike §3, this is not an §4 — it's a direct proof of\n"
"membership. Use it as §5 when the goal is\n"
"§6."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L09_ExtTactic
msgid "Subgroup Extensionality"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `a`
#. §1: `{g | a * g = g * a}`
#. §2: `G`
#. §3: `G`
#. §4: `Z(G)`
#. §5: `Subgroup.center G`
#. §6: `center G = {z : G | ∀ g : G, g * z = z * g}`
#. §7: `Z(G) = G`
#. §8: `G`
#. §9: `Z(G) = {1}`
#. §10: `Subgroup.mem_center_iff`
#. §11: `z ∈ center G ↔ ∀ g, g * z = z * g`
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro
msgid "In the previous worlds, you proved that the *centralizer* of an element\n"
"§0 — the set §1 — is a subgroup. But what if we\n"
"demand more: what if an element commutes with *everything* in §2?\n"
"\n"
"The **center** of a group §3, written §4 in mathematics and\n"
"§5 in Lean, is exactly this:\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"Every element of the center commutes with every element of the group.\n"
"The center is always a subgroup — you'll prove its three closure\n"
"properties in this world.\n"
"\n"
"The center measures how close a group is to being abelian:\n"
"- If §7 (the center is everything), then every pair commutes\n"
"  and §8 is abelian.\n"
"- If §9 (only the identity is central), the group is\n"
"  \"as non-abelian as possible.\"\n"
"\n"
"The gateway lemma is §10:\n"
"\n"
"§11\n"
"\n"
"Every proof in this world starts by converting center membership\n"
"to this universal commuting condition."
msgstr ""

