#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L07_PrimeDichotomy
msgid "Here is a remarkable fact: in a group of prime order, every subgroup\n"
"is either trivial (§0) or the whole group (§1). There is no\n"
"room for anything in between.\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"Why? By Lagrange's theorem (which you'll prove later), the size of\n"
"any subgroup divides the size of the group. If the group has prime\n"
"order §3, the only divisors of §4 are §5 and §6 — so the\n"
"subgroup has size §7 (it's §8) or size §9 (it's §10).\n"
"\n"
"The hypothesis §11 is a **typeclass**\n"
"saying \"it is a fact that §12 is prime.\" Lean synthesizes\n"
"it automatically when it's in scope.\n"
"\n"
"This level also introduces the §13 tactic. When the current\n"
"hypotheses are contradictory, §14 changes any goal to §15.\n"
"You then prove §16 by combining the contradictory hypotheses.\n"
"\n"
"Given a non-trivial subgroup in a prime-order group, show it must\n"
"be the whole group."
