#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L03_Decide
msgid "Later in this world, you'll prove that groups of **prime** order are\n"
"cyclic. To use results about primes, you sometimes need to verify\n"
"that a specific number is prime.\n"
"\n"
"Is §0 prime? You could check by hand: it's not divisible by §1,\n"
"§2, or §3, so yes. But Lean can do this check automatically with\n"
"the §4 tactic.\n"
"\n"
"§5 works on any **decidable** proposition — a statement whose\n"
"truth value can be determined by computation. This includes:\n"
"\n"
"- §6 (is 5 prime?)\n"
"- §7 (is 3 nonzero?)\n"
"- §8 (is 2 less than 7?)\n"
"- equality and inequality of concrete natural numbers\n"
"\n"
"For abstract mathematical objects (like an arbitrary group §9),\n"
"§10 usually can't help — those require proof. But for concrete\n"
"computations, it's the right tool.\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §11 is prime."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `mul_one`
#. §1: `mul_one`
#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial.L01_RightIdentity
msgid "You just used §0, one of the five group axioms. In a group,\n"
"multiplying by the identity on the right does nothing.\n"
"\n"
"Check your inventory — §1 is now available for all future levels."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `ext`
