#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L09_ExtTactic
msgid "How do you prove two subgroups are equal? The **extensionality**\n"
"principle says: two subgroups with the same elements are equal.\n"
"\n"
"The §0 tactic implements this. If the goal is §1 for\n"
"subgroups §2, then §3 reduces it to:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"An §5 (if and only if) goal has two directions. You can split it\n"
"with §6 — the same angle-bracket syntax you already\n"
"know, but now for §7 instead of §8. This creates two goals:\n"
"- Forward: §9\n"
"- Backward: §10\n"
"\n"
"Then use §11 to introduce the hypothesis and prove each direction.\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §12 — intersecting with the whole group changes\n"
"nothing."
msgstr ""

