"§7 creates two goals: §8 and §9.\n"
"\n"
"Think of it as: \"to prove the goal, it suffices to prove §10,\n"
"because §11 turns §12 into §13.\""
msgstr ""

#. §0: `apply inv_eq_of_mul_eq_one_right`
#. §1: `(a * b) * (b⁻¹ * a⁻¹) = 1`
#. §2: `rw [mul_assoc, mul_inv_cancel_left, mul_inv_cancel]`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L09_Boss
msgid "After §0, the\n"
"goal becomes §1. Close it with:\n"
"§2"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `«{a}» * «{x}»⁻¹`
#. §1: `«{x}»⁻¹ * «{x}»`
#. §2: `1`
#. §3: `mul_assoc`
#. §4: `← hx`
#. §5: `«{x}» * «{a}»`
#. §6: `«{a}» * «{x}»`
#. §7: `«{x}» * «{x}»⁻¹`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef.L11_Boss
msgid "Start from §0, insert\n"
"§1 on the left (which is §2), rearrange using\n"
"§3, apply §4 to swap §5 to §6,\n"
"then cancel §7 on the right."
