msgstr ""

#. §0: `f`
#. §1: `ker(f)`
#. §2: `1`
#. §3: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_ker] at hx`
#. §4: `hx : f x = 1`
#. §5: `rw [← map_one f] at hx`
#. §6: `hx : f x = f 1`
#. §7: `exact hf hx`
#. §8: `x = 1`
#. §9: `f(x) = 1 = f(1)`
#. §10: `f`
#. §11: `x = 1`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L06_InjectiveKernel
msgid "If §0 is injective, the only element in §1 is §2.\n"
"\n"
"The pattern:\n"
"1. §3 → §4\n"
"2. §5 → §6\n"
"3. §7 → §8 by injectivity\n"
"\n"
"This is the **backward direction** of the boss theorem:\n"
"*injective → trivial kernel*.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"If §9 and §10 is injective, then §11.\"*"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `f`
#. §1: `f`
#. §2: `f.range = {y ∈ H | ∃ x : G, f(x) = y}`
#. §3: `f.range`
#. §4: `Subgroup H`
#. §5: `MonoidHom.mem_range : y ∈ f.range ↔ ∃ x, f x = y`
#. §6: `f x = 1`
#. §7: `G`
#. §8: `f a`
#. §9: `a`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L04_RangeDef
msgid "The kernel captures what §0 destroys. The **range** captures what\n"
"§1 reaches.\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §3 is a §4. The unfolding lemma is:\n"
"\n"
"§5\n"
"\n"
"Unlike kernel membership (which is a *property check*: does §6?),\n"
"range membership requires producing a **witness** — an element of §7\n"
"that maps to the target.\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §8 is in the range by providing the witness §9."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `h : P ∧ Q`
#. §1: `h.1`
#. §2: `h.2`
#. §3: `obtain`
#. §4: `obtain ⟨hp, hq⟩ := h`
#. §5: `h`
#. §6: `hp : P`
#. §7: `hq : Q`
#. §8: `a ∈ H ⊓ K`
#. §9: `a ∈ K ∧ a ∈ H`
#. §10: `obtain`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L07_ObtainTactic
msgid "When you have a conjunction hypothesis §0, projections like\n"
"§1 and §2 work but can be hard to read. The §3 tactic\n"
"gives you named components instead:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"This replaces §5 with two hypotheses: §6 and §7.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, you have §8 and need to prove §9\n"
"— the conjunction with the two parts **swapped**. The math is\n"
"trivial; the point is to practice §10."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SubgroupDef
msgid "Subgroup Definitions"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `f 1 * f 1 = f 1`
#. §1: `← map_mul`
#. §2: `f 1 * f 1`
#. §3: `f (1 * 1)`
#. §4: `rw [← map_mul]`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L04_MapOne
msgid "The goal is §0. Now rewrite the left side\n"
"using §1: the product §2 becomes §3.\n"
"\n"
"Try §4."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `h : «{g}» = 1`
#. §1: `exact h`
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L04_ZpowersEqBot
msgid "The hypothesis is now §0.\n"
"Use §1."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `f(a) = f(b)`
#. §1: `f(ab⁻¹) = 1`
#. §2: `ab⁻¹ ∈ ker = {1}`
#. §3: `a = b`
#. §4: `f(x) = 1 = f(1)`
#. §5: `f`
#. §6: `x = 1`
#. §7: `f`
#. §8: `f.ker`
#. §9: `{x | f x = 1}`
#. §10: `MonoidHom.mem_ker`
#. §11: `x ∈ f.ker ↔ f x = 1`
#. §12: `f.range`
#. §13: `{y | ∃ x, f x = y}`
#. §14: `MonoidHom.mem_range`
#. §15: `y ∈ f.range ↔ ∃ x, f x = y`
#. §16: `Function.Injective`
#. §17: `∀ a b, f a = f b → a = b`
#. §18: `mul_inv_eq_one`
#. §19: `a * b⁻¹ = 1 ↔ a = b`
#. §20: `specialize`
#. §21: `rw [mem_ker]`
#. §22: `f x = 1`
#. §23: `obtain`
#. §24: `⟨w, proof⟩`
#. §25: ```
#.         x ∈ f.ker
#.        ↗         ↘
#.    f x = 1    x ∈ ⊥
#.        ↘         ↗
#.          x = 1
#. ```
#. §26: `rw`
#. §27: `f`
#. §28: `ker(f)`
#. §29: `f`
#. §30: `f`
#. §31: `0`
#. §32: `1`
#. §33: `f(ab) = f(a)f(b)`
#. §34: `ker(f) = ⊥`
#. §35: `f`
#. §36: `range(f) = ⊤`
#. §37: `f`
#. §38: `G / ker(f) ≅ range(f)`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L08_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing **Kernel and Image**!\n"
"\n"
"You proved the fundamental connection:\n"
"\n"
"> **A group homomorphism is injective if and only if its kernel is trivial.**\n"
"\n"
"Both directions:\n"
"- **ker = ⊥ → injective**: If §0, then\n"
"  §1, so §2, so §3.\n"
"- **injective → ker = ⊥**: If §4 and §5 is\n"
"  injective, then §6.\n"
"\n"
"This theorem says: **the kernel measures exactly the failure of\n"
"injectivity**. The bigger the kernel, the more information §7 loses.\n"
"\n"
"Your tools from this world:\n"
"\n"
"| Item | Type | Purpose |\n"
"|------|------|---------|\n"
"| §8 | Definition | Kernel subgroup: §9 |\n"
"| §10 | Theorem | §11 |\n"
"| §12 | Definition | Range subgroup: §13 |\n"
"| §14 | Theorem | §15 |\n"
"| §16 | Definition | §17 |\n"
"| §18 | Theorem | §19 |\n"
"| §20 | Tactic | Pin a universal hypothesis to a specific value |\n"
"\n"
"Proof moves:\n"
"- **Kernel reasoning**: §21 → algebra → §22\n"
"- **Image reasoning**: §23 witness → transform → §24\n"
"\n"
"The **kernel navigation diamond** summarizes the key equivalences:\n"
"\n"
"§25\n"
"\n"
"Each arrow is one §26 step. The forward direction of the boss\n"
"chains the left side down; the backward direction chains the\n"
"right side down.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"A homomorphism §27 is injective iff §28 is trivial.\n"
"The kernel is the obstruction to injectivity: elements that collapse\n"
"together under §29 differ by a kernel element.\"*\n"
"\n"
"**Important**: this equivalence depends on §30 being a *homomorphism*.\n"
"For an arbitrary function, having only one preimage of §31 (or §32)\n"
"does not imply injectivity. The homomorphism property — §33 —\n"
"is what connects the kernel to global injectivity.\n"
"\n"
"Dually, just as §34 means §35 is injective,\n"
"§36 means §37 is surjective. The kernel measures\n"
"information *destroyed*; the range measures information *reached*.\n"
"\n"
"Looking further ahead: the first isomorphism theorem will make this\n"
"precise — §38, so the kernel is exactly the\n"
"\"redundancy\" that must be collapsed to recover the image.\n"
"\n"
"What's next: you'll practice these skills under varied settings in\n"
"the problem set, then meet *normal* subgroups — a property that\n"
"every kernel automatically has."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `f(a) = f(b)`
#. §1: `f(a * b⁻¹) = 1`
#. §2: `f(a) * f(b) = f(c)`
#. §3: `a * b * c⁻¹`
#. §4: `f`
#. §5: `a * b * c⁻¹`
#. §6: `f(a) * f(b) * f(c)⁻¹`
#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L04_EquationToKernel
msgid "The Homomorphisms boss went from §0 to §1.\n"
"Here's the reverse direction in a different form.\n"
"\n"
"Given an equation §2 in the target group,\n"
"conclude that §3 lands in the kernel.\n"
"\n"
"The idea: push §4 through §5 to get\n"
"§6, then substitute the hypothesis and cancel."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `rw [← inv_eq_of_mul_eq_one_right h]`
#. §1: `b`
#. §2: `a⁻¹`
#. §3: `a⁻¹ * a = 1`
#. §4: `inv_mul_cancel`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasicsPset.L04_RightInvImpliesLeftInv
msgid "Use §0 to\n"
"replace §1 with §2. The goal becomes §3, which is\n"
"§4."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `_ = (a⁻¹ * a) * 1`
#. §1: `1`
#. §2: `a⁻¹ * (a⁻¹)⁻¹`
#. §3: `mul_inv_cancel`
#. §4: ```
#. calc a⁻¹ * a
#. _ = (a⁻¹ * a) * 1                       := by rw [mul_one]
#. _ = (a⁻¹ * a) * (a⁻¹ * (a⁻¹)⁻¹)         := by rw [mul_inv_cancel]
#. _ = ((a⁻¹ * a) * a⁻¹) * (a⁻¹)⁻¹         := by rw [← mul_assoc]
#. ...
#. ```
#. §5: `a`
#. §6: `a⁻¹`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L01_DeriveLeftInverse
msgid "After §0, replace the §1\n"
"with §2 using §3, then re-bracket:\n"
"§4\n"
"The remaining steps bring §5 next to §6, cancel them, and clean up."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Function.Surjective f`
#. §1: `f`
#. §2: `∀ (b : H), ∃ (a : G), f a = b`
#. §3: `hs : Function.Surjective f`
#. §4: `y : H`
#. §5: `hs y`
#. §6: `∃ x, f x = y`
#. §7: `f.range = ⊤`
#: Game.Levels.HomPset.L06_SurjectiveIntoRange
msgid "§0 means §1 hits every element of the\n"
"target:\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"If §3 and §4, then §5\n"
"gives §6.\n"
"\n"
"A group homomorphism is surjective if and only if its range\n"
"is the whole group (§7)."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `apply Subgroup.mem_center_iff.mp`
#. §1: `exact h y`
#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L07_Boss
msgid "Use §0 to reduce the goal\n"
"to a center membership, then close with §1."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `rw [MonoidHom.mem_range]`
#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L04_RangeDef
msgid "Use §0 to unfold range membership."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `H`
#. §1: `K`
#. §2: `G`
#. §3: `Subgroup G`
#. §4: `{g | g ∈ H ∧ g ∈ K}`
#. §5: `apply Subgroup.mk_carrier`
#. §6: `∧`
#. §7: `obtain`
#. §8: `one_mem H`
#. §9: `1 ∈ H`
#. §10: `mul_mem`
#. §11: `x ∈ H → y ∈ H → x * y ∈ H`
#. §12: `inv_mem`
#. §13: `x ∈ H → x⁻¹ ∈ H`
#. §14: `Subgroup.mk_carrier`
#. §15: `apply`
#. §16: `intro`
#. §17: `show`
#. §18: `obtain ⟨_, _⟩`
#. §19: `∧`
#. §20: `exact ⟨_, _⟩`
#. §21: `∧`
#: Game.Levels.SubgroupBasics.L11_Boss
msgid "Time to put it all together. Given two subgroups §0 and §1 of §2,\n"
"construct the **intersection subgroup** from scratch — a §3\n"
"whose carrier is §4.\n"
"\n"
"Use §5 as in the previous world, but with\n"
"a twist: the carrier predicate involves §6, so each closure proof\n"
"starts by destructuring the conjunction hypotheses using §7.\n"
"\n"
"Your toolkit for this level:\n"
"\n"
"| Theorem | Statement |\n"
"|---------|-----------|\n"
"| §8 | §9 |\n"
"| §10 | §11 |\n"
"| §12 | §13 |\n"
"\n"
"| Tactic | Use |\n"
"|--------|-----|\n"
"| §14 | Set up the subgroup with §15 |\n"
"| §16 | Introduce elements and hypotheses |\n"
"| §17 | Unfold membership (optional) |\n"
"| §18 | Destructure §19 hypotheses |\n"
"| §20 | Build §21 goals |"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.CenterIntro.L05_CenterEqTop
msgid "Abelian Groups Have Full Center"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `rw [pow_succ, pow_succ, pow_succ, ih, mul_mul_mul_comm]`
#. §1: `pow_succ`
#. §2: `ih`
#. §3: `a ^ «{n}» * b ^ «{n}» * (a * b) = a ^ «{n}» * a * (b ^ «{n}» * b)`
#. §4: `mul_mul_mul_comm`
#. §5: `calc`
#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L06_Boss
msgid "The full induction step in one line:\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"After the three §1 rewrites and §2, the goal becomes\n"
"§3.\n"
"The interchange law §4 rearranges the left side\n"
"to match.\n"
"\n"
"Alternatively, you can write a §5 proof handling each\n"
"rewrite as a separate step."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `map_one`
#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L04_MapOne
msgid "Deriving §0"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `induction`
#. §1: ```
#. induction n with
#. | zero => -- prove the base case (n = 0)
#. | succ n ih => -- prove the step case, with ih as the hypothesis
#. ```
#. §2: `ih`
#. §3: `n`
#. §4: `n + 1`
#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L04_OnePow
msgid "The §0 tactic performs induction on a natural number\n"
"(or any inductive type).\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"§2 is the **induction hypothesis**: the statement for §3 that\n"
"you can use to prove the statement for §4."
