#. §0: `zpowers g = ⊤`
#. §1: `IsCyclic`
#. §2: `H`
#. §3: `zpowers g`
#. §4: `H.eq_bot_or_eq_top_of_prime_card`
#. §5: `(zpowers g).eq_bot_or_eq_top_of_prime_card`
#. §6: `⊥`
#. §7: `exact hne hbot`
#. §8: `rw [zpowers_eq_bot] at hbot; exfalso; exact hg hbot`
#. §9: `⊤`
#. §10: `exact htop`
#. §11: `exact htop`
#. §12: `⊥`
#. §13: `zpowers g = ⊥`
#. §14: `g = 1`
#. §15: `zpowers_eq_bot`
#. §16: `hg : g ≠ 1`
#. §17: `hbot : zpowers g = ⊥`
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L08_ZpowersTopOfPrime
msgid "You proved that in a prime-order group, any non-identity element\n"
"generates the whole group: §0.\n"
"\n"
"This is the **core argument** of the boss level. The only remaining\n"
"step will be wrapping it in the §1 characterization.\n"
"\n"
"Compare this proof with the last level:\n"
"\n"
"| Step | L7 (abstract §2) | L8 (§3) |\n"
"|------|-------------------|------------------|\n"
"| Dichotomy | §4 | §5 |\n"
"| Rule out §6 | §7 | §8 |\n"
"| Conclude §9 | §10 | §11 |\n"
"\n"
"The extra step in the §12 case — converting §13 to\n"
"§14 via §15 — is the key technique. You can't\n"
"directly apply §16 to §17 without\n"
"first translating between the subgroup-level and element-level\n"
"statements."
