"\n"
"If the goal is §1, you can write §2 to\n"
"unfold the set membership into the underlying predicate.\n"
"\n"
"This is useful when the goal looks opaque (e.g., §3) and you\n"
"want to see what it *really* means.\n"
"\n"
"§4 does not change the proof state — it only changes how the\n"
"goal is displayed. If the statement you provide is not definitionally\n"
"equal to the current goal, §5 will fail."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `a * b * c`
#. §1: `c * b * a`
#. §2: `mul_comm`
#. §3: `rw [mul_comm (a * b) c]`
#. §4: `(a * b)`
#. §5: `c`
#. §6: `a`
#. §7: `b`
#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L02_CommRearrange
msgid "You need to rearrange §0 to §1. The key\n"
"skill: provide arguments to §2 to target specific swaps.\n"
"\n"
"Try §3 to swap §4 with §5.\n"
"Then swap §6 and §7."
