#. §6: `g ^ orderOf g = 1`
#. §7: `g`
#. §8: `1`
#. §9: `orderOf_one`
#. §10: `orderOf (1 : G) = 1`
#. §11: `1`
#. §12: `1^1 = 1`
#. §13: `pow_orderOf_eq_one`
#. §14: `g ^ (2 * orderOf g) = 1`
#. §15: `g ^ (2 * orderOf g) = (g ^ orderOf g) ^ 2 = 1 ^ 2 = 1`
#. §16: `pow_mul`
#. §17: `g ^ (2 * orderOf g)`
#. §18: `(g ^ orderOf g) ^ 2`
#. §19: `pow_mul`
#. §20: `a ^ (m * n) = (a ^ m) ^ n`
#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups.L05_OrderOf
msgid "Every element of a group has an **order**: the smallest positive\n"
"integer §0 such that §1. In Lean, this is §2.\n"
"\n"
"If no such §3 exists (the element has infinite order), then\n"
"§4 by convention.\n"
"\n"
"Two key lemmas:\n"
"\n"
"- §5: §6\n"
"  (the defining property — raising §7 to its order gives §8)\n"
"\n"
"- §9: §10\n"
"  (the identity has order §11 since §12)\n"
"\n"
"Given §13, prove that §14.\n"
"The idea: §15.\n"
"\n"
"You'll need §16 to rewrite §17 as\n"
"§18. (Remember: §19 is for ℕ-powers, saying\n"
"§20.)"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `inv_inj`
#. §1: `a⁻¹ = b⁻¹ ↔ a = b`
#. §2: `→`
#. §3: `exact inv_inj.mp h`
#. §4: `a⁻¹ = b⁻¹`
#. §5: `a = b`
#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics.L08_InvInv
msgid "§0 says §1 — the inverse function is\n"
"injective.\n"
"\n"
"Use the §2 direction with §3 to go from\n"
"§4 to §5."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `«{ih}» : f (a ^ n) = 1`
#. §1: `f (a ^ (n + 1)) = 1`
#. §2: `a ^ (n + 1)`
